----------------------
  Selenium WebDriver    
----------------------

What is selenium webdriver?
Selenium WebDriver is an open-source framework and API that allows developers to write code which can launch browsers, navigate pages, interact with web elements, and verify outcomes—mimicking the actions of a real user
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1) WebDriver is one of the component in selenium.
2) WebDriver is a java interface.
3) WebDriver is an API( Application Programming interface)
(API that interacts directly with browsers using dedicated browser drivers like ChromeDriver, FirefoxDriver, etc)
webdriver api java script--> api-->web browser

WebDriver API: A set of programming interfaces for controlling browsers in automation scripts.
This API provides the essential functions for browser control, including launching URLs, retrieving titles, finding elements, and closing sessions. 
Maven: A build automation tool that manages project dependencies through pom.xml.
ChromeDriver/FirefoxDriver: Browser-specific drivers that implement the WebDriver interface for automation

Search context  --> webDriver(I) -- RemoteWebDriver(C)---->ChromeDriver , FirefoxDriver, EdgeDriver etc..
 (interface)        (interface)     (implements)                      (inherited)
--------------------------------
          (abstract class)
Environment setup
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1) Downloading jars files and attaching them to Java project.(Manually) - Not recomended
- Download Selenium WebDriver JAR files.
- Create a new Java project in an IDE (like Eclipse).
- Attach these JARs to the project’s build path


2) Creating Maven project   ( Recomended )
(mvn repository for dependencies) https://mvnrepository.com/ ---> selenium java
- Created a new Maven project in eclipse
- addedd webdriver dependecy in pom.xml--> updated
- pom.xml ---> dependencies

Assignment
--------------
1) Launch browser (chrome)
2) Open URL  https://demo.nopcommerce.com/
3) Validate title should be   "nopCommerce demo store"
4) close page


import org.openqa.selenium.WebDriver;
import org.openqa.selenium.chrome.ChromeDriver;

public class SeleniumDemo {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        // Set system property for ChromeDriver
        System.setProperty("webdriver.chrome.driver", "path/to/chromedriver.exe");

        // Initialize WebDriver
        WebDriver driver = new ChromeDriver();

        // 1. Launch browser and 2. Open URL
        driver.get("https://demo.nopcommerce.com/");

        // 3. Validate title
        String expectedTitle = "nopCommerce demo store";
        String actualTitle = driver.getTitle();

        if(actualTitle.equals(expectedTitle)){
            System.out.println("Title validation successful!");
        } else {
            System.out.println("Title validation failed. Actual Title: " + actualTitle);
        }

        // 4. Close browser
        driver.quit();
    }
}


